claim.claim-text:
1. An oxide etch process for etching an oxide layer over a non-oxide layer, comprising the steps of: 
flowing into a plasma reaction chamber an etching gas mixture comprising (a) a heavy fluorocarbon selected from the group consisting of hexafluorobutadiene, hexafluorocyclobutene, and hexafluorobenzene, (b) a hydrofluoromethane, (c) a polymerization counteracting gas selected from the group of oxygen gas and nitrogen gas; and (d) a chemically inactive gas selected from the group of argon and xenon, a diluent flow of said chemically inactive gas being at least equal to an active flow of said heavy fluorocarbon; 
RF biasing a pedestal electrode supporting a substrate having an oxide layer overlying a nitride layer and exciting said etching gas mixture into a plasma to thereby etch said oxide layer selectively to said non-oxide layer.
